-- Zimbabwe Plans to Scrap Levy on Imports, Newsday Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-02-10T11:32:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-10/zimbabwe-plans-to-scrap-levy-on-imports-newsday-reports.html
Zimbabwe plans to scrap a levy on
imported used vehicles and some foods after complaints from
retailers,  Newsday  reported, citing Commerce Minister  Welshman Ncube .  The southern African nation added a 25 percent levy to the
normal import tax on those products last month, the Harare-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
